  {panel}

*Problem Statement*

Currently, administrators can only choose which fields will appear when a customer opens a request on the Customer Portal. It might be useful if administrators could configure a 'next' button to take the user to a different screen based on the inputs in the first screen instead of creating a ticket right after.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Service Desk Server*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDCLOUD-4122].
  {panel}

I read this feature is happening in the next update. Is there an ETA as to when this will occur? This will directly affect the way we currently rollout out new workflow.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Service Desk Server*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDCLOUD-4121].
  {panel}

Currently the Requested Participant field is a Multi User Picker. We have some use cases where a reporter would like to add their JIRA group/team as a participant to the reported issue rather than adding each member of their team individually. 

A simplified solution would be to allow for groups to be selected with the UI and upon submitting the users in the group get added to the Requested Participant field individually.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Service Desk Server*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDCLOUD-4115].
  {panel}

JIRA Core publishes on at https://docs.atlassian.com/jira/REST/cloud/jira-rest-plugin.wadl - it would be awesome for us to get one for JSD.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Service Desk Server*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDCLOUD-4114].
