h3. Problem Definition

The [Who receives service desk notifications|https://confluence.atlassian.com/servicedeskcloud/managing-service-desk-notifications-732528936.html#Managingservicedesknotifications-Whoreceivesservicedesknotifications] states that:
{quote}
When agents work on an issue, they receive email notifications as part of the the project's JIRA notification scheme.
{quote}

However, it does not clarify that an agent in Service Desk project will be treated as customer in an issue where it's the reporter, regarding notifications.

This will have, for example, the effect that this user will not be notified of it's own comments, even if he has the {{My Changes}} option in its profile set to {{Notify me}}, as JIRA notifications won't apply. Check [JSD-4105|https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSD-4105].

h3. Suggested Solution
Update documentation to add a warning saying (something like):
{quote}
An agent will be notified as a customer for issues it's a reporter of
{quote}

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Service Desk Server*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDCLOUD-4110].
  {panel}

